<p>Heading into the final day of the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/2006%E2%80%9307_Eredivisie" title=3D"2006=E2=80=9307 Eredivisie">2006=E2=
=80=9307 Eredivisie</a> season, three teams were still in contention to win=
 the title, and with it a guaranteed place in the 2007=E2=80=9308 UEFA Cham=
pions League. PSV, looking to win their third straight league title, was th=
e only one of the three to play its final match at home, against <a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vitesse_Arnhem" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=
=3D"Vitesse Arnhem">Vitesse Arnhem</a>. Ajax, looking to win their first ti=
tle since 2004, traveled to <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Willem=
_II_(football_club)" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Willem II (football clu=
b)">Willem II</a>, while AZ faced Excelsior looking to win its first league=
 title since 1981, after finishing in the top three in the previous two sea=
sons.
</p><p>These final matches were played on April 29, 2007. AZ struggled agai=
nst <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/S.B.V._Excelsior" class=3D"mw-=
redirect" title=3D"S.B.V. Excelsior">Excelsior</a> (who would have to go th=
rough a relegation play-off after the end of the game) as they played almos=
t 72 minutes of the match with only 10 men, as goalkeeper <a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boy_Waterman" title=3D"Boy Waterman">Boy Waterman</=
a> was red-carded in the 18th minute. AZ came from behind twice, with <a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Danny_Koevermans" title=3D"Danny Koever=
mans">Danny Koevermans</a> tying the match in the 70th minute with his 22nd=
 goal of the season. AZ had a chance to take the lead after its numerical d=
isadvantage was leveled as Excelsior's Rene van Dieren was sent off for yel=
low card accumulation. AZ never took advantage and a goal from Johan Voskam=
p in the 90th minute gave Excelsior a shock 3=E2=80=932 win.<sup id=3D"cite=
_ref-5" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Goal_d=
ifference#cite_note-5"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>5<span class=3D=
"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>Meanwhile, in Tilburg, Ajax took the lead in the 18th minute with a =
goal from Urby Emanuelson. Ajax added a second goal in the 69th minute as <=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Klaas-Jan_Huntelaar" title=3D"Klaas=
-Jan Huntelaar">Klaas-Jan Huntelaar</a> scored his 21st goal of the season.=
<sup id=3D"cite_ref-6" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/Goal_difference#cite_note-6"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>=
6<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>Meanwhile, PSV scored twice in the first 10 minutes, but gave up a g=
oal three minutes later and led only 2=E2=80=931 at half-time. In the secon=
d half, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ibrahim_Afellay" title=3D"=
Ibrahim Afellay">Ibrahim Afellay</a> scored in the 58th minute before anoth=
er goal from Jefferson Farfan made the score 4=E2=80=931 to PSV.<sup id=3D"=
cite_ref-7" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Go=
al_difference#cite_note-7"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>7<span clas=
s=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>Following Huntelaar's 69th-minute goal, PSV and Ajax were level on p=
oints and goal difference, but Ajax had a superior goals scored. But in the=
 77th minute, Philip Cocu put PSV up 5=E2=80=931 and the team was up on goa=
l difference (+50 to Ajax's +49). The scores stayed that way at full time, =
and so PSV won the 2006=E2=80=9307 <i>Eredivisie</i> in one of the most exc=
iting finishes to a season in recent memory.
<link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r=
1011077906">
