<p>The <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2010_%C3%9Arvalsdeild" titl=
e=3D"2010 =C3=9Arvalsdeild">2010 =C3=9Arvalsdeild</a> season concluded on S=
eptember 25, 2010, and three teams were still in contention to win the leag=
ue title. Leading the table was Brei=C3=B0ablik, based in <a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/K%C3%B3pavogur" title=3D"K=C3=B3pavogur">K=C3=B3pav=
ogur</a>, who knew that a win would give them their first ever league title=
. Trailing one point behind were =C3=8DBV from <a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/Vestmannaeyjar" title=3D"Vestmannaeyjar">Vestmannaeyjar</a>, w=
ho were looking to win their fourth league title, but its first since 1998.=
 In third place was two-time defending champions FH, looking to win the lea=
gue title, but trailing Brei=C3=B0ablik by only two points.
</p><p>Brei=C3=B0ablik traveled to <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/Stjarnan" title=3D"Stjarnan">Stjarnan</a> and were held to a scoreless dra=
w, but would get encouraging news. Playing their final game at <a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Keflav%C3%ADk" title=3D"Keflav=C3=ADk">Keflav=
=C3=ADk</a>, =C3=8DBV were losing 2=E2=80=930 with 16 minutes remaining whe=
n Denis Sytnik scored for =C3=8DBV to cut the deficit to 2=E2=80=931. But t=
