pan></span></div>
<p>The <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2011%E2%80%9312_Premier_Lea=
gue" title=3D"2011=E2=80=9312 Premier League">2011=E2=80=9312 Premier Leagu=
e</a> was largely a two-horse race contested between <a href=3D"https://en.=
wikipedia.org/wiki/Manchester_City_F.C." title=3D"Manchester City F.C.">Man=
chester City</a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Manchester_Un=
ited" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Manchester United">Manchester United</=
a> for most of the season, with both clubs finishing 19 points ahead of thi=
rd-placed <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arsenal_F.C." title=3D"A=
rsenal F.C.">Arsenal</a>. City and United went into their final matches of =
the season level on points, but with City in first-place due to a goal diff=
erence superior by +8. The final matches were relegation threatened <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Queens_Park_Rangers" class=3D"mw-redirect=
" title=3D"Queens Park Rangers">Queens Park Rangers</a> at home for City, a=
nd <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sunderland_A.F.C." title=3D"Sun=
derland A.F.C.">Sunderland</a> away for United. City were strong favourites=
, with United's manager <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alex_Fergu=
son" title=3D"Alex Ferguson">Alex Ferguson</a> stating City would have to d=
o 'something stupid' not to beat QPR.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-13" class=3D"refer=
ence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Goal_difference#cite_note-13=
"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>13<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</sp=
an></a></sup>
</p><p>A Manchester City win would guarantee the title due to a realistical=
ly unassailable superior goal difference. If not a win, then City just need=
ed to match United's result at the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/Stadium_of_Light" title=3D"Stadium of Light">Stadium of Light</a> against =
Sunderland or have United lose against Sunderland. United scored in the 20t=
h minute, winning 1=E2=80=930. City scored two goals in injury time to come=
 from behind and win 3=E2=80=932.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-14" class=3D"reference=
"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Goal_difference#cite_note-14"><s=
pan class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>14<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span><=
/a></sup>
</p>
