w-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Red_Star_Belgrade" title=3D"Red=
 Star Belgrade">Red Star Belgrade</a> won the <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/1951_Yugoslav_First_League" title=3D"1951 Yugoslav First League=
">1951 Yugoslav First League</a> championship ahead of <a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/wiki/GNK_Dinamo_Zagreb" title=3D"GNK Dinamo Zagreb">Dinamo =
Zagreb</a> with a 0.013 better goal average. Dinamo's final match against <=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/OFK_Beograd" title=3D"OFK Beograd">=
BSK Belgrade</a> ended in a 2=E2=80=932 draw, and the following day Red Sta=
r defeated <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/FK_Partizan" title=3D"F=
K Partizan">Partizan</a> 2=E2=80=930, meaning that both teams finished on 3=
5 points. Red Star's 50 goals for and 21 against gave a goal average of 2.3=
81, while Dinamo's 45 to 19 gave 2.368.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-17" class=3D"ref=
erence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Goal_difference#cite_note-=
17"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>17<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</=
span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-18" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Goal_difference#cite_note-18"><span class=3D"cite-=
bracket">[</span>18<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
